      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DO IT FOR YOU (5) was six weeks between runs and went up sharply in grade but almost pulled off a third straight win when edged out by RESURRECTED here at this trip recently. Nicely drawn and gets a weight swing today so he is perfectly placed to turn the tables. The consistent PRESSALONG (6) won over the mile at Grafton two back then caught the eye late over a shorter trip there last time. Worth plenty of thought stepping back up in trip. RESURRECTED (1) appreciated the step up in trip last start when he led for home and defied all challengers in a similar race to this. Has won six races and all have been on rain-affected surfaces, so today's good track isn't optimal. BEAN FOGGY (3) has struggled at his last couple in better company. Last raced in a BM82 three back when in the money over 1550m at Murwillumbah. Right in contention on that effort. Market watch on FLYING BAT (7) first-up from a short break with very little on his back after Heinrich's claim.",
